  "text": "Cytoplasmic dynein is similarly complex and consists of a homodimer of heavy chains, a dimer of a WD repeat intermediate chains, four light intermediate chains (not 1 has been shown to mediate the dynein-dynactin interaction via direct association with p150 glued [CITATION_1] . Dynactin is a multisubunit complex that may play a role in organelle transport and dynein subcellular localization (for review see [CITATION_2] . However, the regulation and role of this dynein-dynactin interaction within the context of dynein function is not clear.",
